verbs.description: oversocialize (third-person singular simple present oversocializes, present participle oversocializing, simple past and past participle oversocialized)

entries.meaning: (transitive) to make someone socialize too much
examples: "Because of the tendency to oversocialize females in our society, girls learn early to (over)control impulses, to be tractable, obedient, cautious, and self-sacrificing."
